data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value: PINs map which characters get switched with each other for encryption/decryption. Erase this text and paste your PIN into this box. It should be 501 characters and made up of 1s and 0s. Then press "Use Custom PIN" below and you will see the current PIN change. Alternatively, you can generate a random one by pressing "Generate Random Pin". This is a safe method.

data.name: textBox3.Text
data.value:
********************************************************************* **** HOW TO USE LORENZ ENCRYPTION MACHINE SAFETLY **** *********************************************************************
** NOTE: Saving and loading of configurations is not available in ** ** This particular build, sorry guys! **
Tom Taylor - 2014 www.tom189.comuf.com
Hello and welcome to the Lorenz SZ40 Cipher Machine! This program simulates the physical Nazi encryption machine that was the successor to the Enigma machine. Don't worry, the Brits eventually decrypted this one too!
You can use this tool to encrypt your own text using the same methods as the machine did back then. This readme guide will take you through the steps to create a perfectly encrypted piece of text and how to decrypt it for viewing afterwards.
Step 1) Randomise the initial wheel positions. To do this, go to the "Initial Wheel Positions" tab in the menu bar and hit the randomise button. You will notice the numbers of the wheel positions change. This switches the state of the machine to a random one so that people using the same settings as you won't be able to read your personal text.
Step 2) Randomise the PIN data. The PIN data determines which letters are switched with each other to produce a random block of text. Go to the "PIN Data" tab and hit the randomise button. The block of 501 characters will change and voila! A random PIN to use.
Step 3) Save your configuration. Now that you have your own personal machine set up, its wise to save this settings so that any text you encrypt can be decrypted again whenever you'd like. Go to the "Configuration File" tab, hit "Save" and give your configuration a name.
** Congrats! ** You have your own personal Lorenz Machine configuration! You can now type text into the text box on the main form and encrypt/decrypt text at your own volition! Enjoy and give me a tweet (@tom189) if you liked the simulation!
Tom Taylor - 2015

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value: Type text here and press "Encrypt". Once you've done this the text will be encrypted using the Lorenz SZ40 Cipher Machine. You can decrypt it back to normal text by pressing the "Decrypt" button. You can play around with the settings of the machine in the settings panel to the right.
